00:01:08.700 --> 00:01:12.880
So I'll start with Academic BlueSky.

00:01:12.900 --> 00:01:15.480
So the backstory for this project is really that Nikhil and

00:01:15.480 --> 00:01:18.680
I had been doing a project researching fairness and recommendation.

00:01:18.700 --> 00:01:20.830
It was a theory project, which is my kind of original

00:01:20.850 --> 00:01:24.080
research area, and we had worked with a master student who

00:01:24.080 --> 00:01:26.380
built a recommender for archive preprints.

00:01:26.400 --> 00:01:29.830
And we used this to simulate kind of market outcomes in this

00:01:29.830 --> 00:01:31.960
like recommendation system.

00:01:31.980 --> 00:01:34.460
And we were curious, what happens in real data?

00:01:34.480 --> 00:01:38.420
How can we study the fairness outcomes in attention markets on a

00:01:38.420 --> 00:01:39.720
real deployed system?

00:01:39.740 --> 00:01:40.480
How do we experiment?

00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:44.440
And what this really looks like in the literature is either you

00:01:44.440 --> 00:01:48.130
run a lab experiment, you build some sort of simulated recommend

00:01:48.130 --> 00:01:51.730
er, you get people to interact with it and see their

00:01:51.730 --> 00:01:52.360
behavior.

00:01:52.370 --> 00:01:56.850
Another option is to deploy browser extensions.

00:01:56.880 --> 00:02:00.220
So on Twitter, you get someone to download your extension and

00:02:00.310 --> 00:02:04.280
engage with Twitter and you will like manually or you will academically

00:02:04.280 --> 00:02:07.030
re-rank the post that Twitter is returning.

00:02:07.080 --> 00:02:09.050
And this is, you know, also friction-full because

00:02:09.120 --> 00:02:12.460
you have to recruit participants and get them to download the extension

00:02:12.670 --> 00:02:15.040
and engage with it.

00:02:15.060 --> 00:02:19.380
And then the final option is to collaborate with a platform.

00:02:19.400 --> 00:02:22.470
But these are kind of few, these opportunities are few and

00:02:22.470 --> 00:02:24.520
far between.

00:02:24.540 --> 00:02:29.340
So suddenly, November, 2024, many academics were using blue

00:02:29.370 --> 00:02:34.800
sky and in particular, looking for a personalized academic experience,

00:02:34.820 --> 00:02:37.040
which is something that we were really excited about building.

00:02:37.050 --> 00:02:41.530
And so Nikila had this idea, let's build a

00:02:41.530 --> 00:02:43.580
custom feed for academics on blue sky.

00:02:43.600 --> 00:02:47.360
And so we had a little hackathon and built paper sky

00:02:47.360 --> 00:02:50.970
just which is a custom feed for academics showing posts about papers

00:02:50.970 --> 00:02:52.520
